
''''
name= "leo messi"
print(name.title())
''''
output : Leo Messi

when entering user data, generally use name.lower() for a consistent data entry. you don't know what format the user might have entered in the system.

''''
test= "  tester   "
print(test.strip() + "s")
print(test.lstrip() + "s")
print(test.rstrip() + "s")
''''

Output:
testers
tester   s
  testers

